  25:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****   ==============================================================================
  26:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  27:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****   ==============================================================================
  28:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****   [..]
  29:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     The USART HAL driver can be used as follows:
  30:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  31:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (#) Declare a USART_HandleTypeDef handle structure (eg. USART_HandleTypeDef husart).
  32:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (#) Initialize the USART low level resources by implementing the HAL_USART_MspInit() API:
ARM GAS  C:\WINDOWS\ccnv4A6V.s 			page 2


  33:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****         (##) Enable the USARTx interface clock.
  34:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****         (##) USART pins configuration:
  35:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Enable the clock for the USART GPIOs.
  36:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Configure the USART pins as alternate function pull-up.
  37:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****         (##) NVIC configuration if you need to use interrupt process (HAL_USART_Transmit_IT(),
  38:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              HAL_USART_Receive_IT() and HAL_USART_TransmitReceive_IT() APIs):
  39:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Configure the USARTx interrupt priority.
  40:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Enable the NVIC USART IRQ handle.
  41:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****         (##) DMA Configuration if you need to use DMA process (HAL_USART_Transmit_DMA()
  42:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              HAL_USART_Receive_DMA() and HAL_USART_TransmitReceive_DMA() APIs):
  43:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Declare a DMA handle structure for the Tx/Rx channel.
  44:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Enable the DMAx interface clock.
  45:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Configure the declared DMA handle structure with the required Tx/Rx parameters.
  46:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Configure the DMA Tx/Rx channel.
  47:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Associate the initialized DMA handle to the USART DMA Tx/Rx handle.
  48:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Configure the priority and enable the NVIC for the transfer complete interrupt o
  49:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              (+++) Configure the USARTx interrupt priority and enable the NVIC USART IRQ handle
  50:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****                    (used for last byte sending completion detection in DMA non circular mode)
  51:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  52:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (#) Program the Baud Rate, Word Length, Stop Bit, Parity, Hardware
  53:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****         flow control and Mode(Receiver/Transmitter) in the husart Init structure.
  54:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  55:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (#) Initialize the USART registers by calling the HAL_USART_Init() API:
  56:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****         (++) These APIs configures also the low level Hardware GPIO, CLOCK, CORTEX...etc)
  57:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              by calling the customized HAL_USART_MspInit(&husart) API.
  58:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  59:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****         -@@- The specific USART interrupts (Transmission complete interrupt,
  60:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              RXNE interrupt and Error Interrupts) will be managed using the macros
  61:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****              __HAL_USART_ENABLE_IT() and __HAL_USART_DISABLE_IT() inside the transmit and receive p
  62:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  63:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (#) Three operation modes are available within this driver :
  64:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  65:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      *** Polling mode IO operation ***
  66:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      =================================
  67:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      [..]
  68:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) Send an amount of data in blocking mode using HAL_USART_Transmit()
  69:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) Receive an amount of data in blocking mode using HAL_USART_Receive()
  70:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  71:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      *** Interrupt mode IO operation ***
  72:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      ===================================
  73:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      [..]
  74:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) Send an amount of data in non blocking mode using HAL_USART_Transmit_IT()
  75:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) At transmission end of transfer HAL_USART_TxHalfCpltCallback is executed and user can
  76:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****             add his own code by customization of function pointer HAL_USART_TxCpltCallback
  77:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) Receive an amount of data in non blocking mode using HAL_USART_Receive_IT()
  78:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) At reception end of transfer HAL_USART_RxCpltCallback is executed and user can
  79:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****             add his own code by customization of function pointer HAL_USART_RxCpltCallback
  80:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) In case of transfer Error, HAL_USART_ErrorCallback() function is executed and user can
  81:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****             add his own code by customization of function pointer HAL_USART_ErrorCallback
  82:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  83:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      *** DMA mode IO operation ***
  84:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      ==============================
  85:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      [..]
  86:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) Send an amount of data in non blocking mode (DMA) using HAL_USART_Transmit_DMA()
  87:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) At transmission end of half transfer HAL_USART_TxHalfCpltCallback is executed and user c
  88:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****             add his own code by customization of function pointer HAL_USART_TxHalfCpltCallback
  89:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) At transmission end of transfer HAL_USART_TxCpltCallback is executed and user can
ARM GAS  C:\WINDOWS\ccnv4A6V.s 			page 3


  90:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****             add his own code by customization of function pointer HAL_USART_TxCpltCallback
  91:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) Receive an amount of data in non blocking mode (DMA) using HAL_USART_Receive_DMA()
  92:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) At reception end of half transfer HAL_USART_RxHalfCpltCallback is executed and user can
  93:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****             add his own code by customization of function pointer HAL_USART_RxHalfCpltCallback
  94:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) At reception end of transfer HAL_USART_RxCpltCallback is executed and user can
  95:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****             add his own code by customization of function pointer HAL_USART_RxCpltCallback
  96:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) In case of transfer Error, HAL_USART_ErrorCallback() function is executed and user can
  97:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****             add his own code by customization of function pointer HAL_USART_ErrorCallback
  98:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) Pause the DMA Transfer using HAL_USART_DMAPause()
  99:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) Resume the DMA Transfer using HAL_USART_DMAResume()
 100:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) Stop the DMA Transfer using HAL_USART_DMAStop()
