 102:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      *** USART HAL driver macros list ***
 103:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      =============================================
 104:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      [..]
 105:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        Below the list of most used macros in USART HAL driver.
 106:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 107:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) __HAL_USART_ENABLE: Enable the USART peripheral
 108:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) __HAL_USART_DISABLE: Disable the USART peripheral
 109:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) __HAL_USART_GET_FLAG : Check whether the specified USART flag is set or not
 110:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) __HAL_USART_CLEAR_FLAG : Clear the specified USART pending flag
 111:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) __HAL_USART_ENABLE_IT: Enable the specified USART interrupt
 112:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (+) __HAL_USART_DISABLE_IT: Disable the specified USART interrupt
 113:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 114:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      [..]
 115:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (@) You can refer to the USART HAL driver header file for more useful macros
 116:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 117:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     ##### Callback registration #####
 118:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     ==================================
 119:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 120:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 121:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     The compilation define USE_HAL_USART_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 122:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 123:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 124:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 125:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     Use Function @ref HAL_USART_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback.
 126:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     Function @ref HAL_USART_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 127:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxHalfCpltCallback        : Tx Half Complete Callback.
 128:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback            : Tx Complete Callback.
 129:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) RxHalfCpltCallback        : Rx Half Complete Callback.
 130:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback            : Rx Complete Callback.
 131:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxRxCpltCallback          : Tx Rx Complete Callback.
 132:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : Error Callback.
 133:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) AbortCpltCallback         : Abort Complete Callback.
 134:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : USART MspInit.
 135:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : USART MspDeInit.
 136:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 137:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     and a pointer to the user callback function.
 138:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 139:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 140:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     Use function @ref HAL_USART_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 141:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     weak (surcharged) function.
 142:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     @ref HAL_USART_UnRegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 143:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     and the Callback ID.
 144:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 145:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxHalfCpltCallback        : Tx Half Complete Callback.
 146:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback            : Tx Complete Callback.
ARM GAS  C:\WINDOWS\ccnv4A6V.s 			page 4


 147:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) RxHalfCpltCallback        : Rx Half Complete Callback.
 148:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback            : Rx Complete Callback.
 149:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxRxCpltCallback          : Tx Rx Complete Callback.
 150:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : Error Callback.
 151:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) AbortCpltCallback         : Abort Complete Callback.
 152:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : USART MspInit.
 153:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : USART MspDeInit.
 154:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 155:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 156:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     By default, after the @ref HAL_USART_Init() and when the state is HAL_USART_STATE_RESET
 157:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak (surcharged) functions:
 158:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     examples @ref HAL_USART_TxCpltCallback(), @ref HAL_USART_RxHalfCpltCallback().
 159:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are respectively
 160:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     reset to the legacy weak (surcharged) functions in the @ref HAL_USART_Init()
 161:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     and @ref HAL_USART_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 162:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the @ref HAL_USART_Init() and @ref HAL_USART_DeInit(
 163:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand).
 164:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 165:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 166:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_USART_STATE_READY state only.
 167:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 168:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     in HAL_USART_STATE_READY or HAL_USART_STATE_RESET state, thus registered (user)
 169:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 170:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 171:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     using @ref HAL_USART_RegisterCallback() before calling @ref HAL_USART_DeInit()
 172:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     or @ref HAL_USART_Init() function.
 173:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 174:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 175:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     When The compilation define USE_HAL_USART_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 176:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     not defined, the callback registration feature is not available
 177:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     and weak (surcharged) callbacks are used.
 178:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 179:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****   @endverbatim
 180:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****      [..]
 181:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****        (@) Additional remark: If the parity is enabled, then the MSB bit of the data written
 182:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****            in the data register is transmitted but is changed by the parity bit.
 183:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****            Depending on the frame length defined by the M bit (8-bits or 9-bits),
 184:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****            the possible USART frame formats are as listed in the following table:
 185:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     +-------------------------------------------------------------+
 186:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     |   M bit |  PCE bit  |            USART frame                 |
 187:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     |---------------------|---------------------------------------|
 188:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     |    0    |    0      |    | SB | 8 bit data | STB |          |
 189:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     |---------|-----------|---------------------------------------|
 190:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     |    0    |    1      |    | SB | 7 bit data | PB | STB |     |
 191:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     |---------|-----------|---------------------------------------|
 192:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     |    1    |    0      |    | SB | 9 bit data | STB |          |
