 263:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****               ##### Initialization and Configuration functions #####
 264:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****   ==============================================================================
 265:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****   [..]
 266:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****   This subsection provides a set of functions allowing to initialize the USART
 267:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****   in asynchronous and in synchronous modes.
 268:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****   (+) For the asynchronous mode only these parameters can be configured:
 269:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****       (++) Baud Rate
 270:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****       (++) Word Length
 271:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****       (++) Stop Bit
 272:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****       (++) Parity: If the parity is enabled, then the MSB bit of the data written
 273:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****            in the data register is transmitted but is changed by the parity bit.
 274:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****            Depending on the frame length defined by the M bit (8-bits or 9-bits),
 275:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****            please refer to Reference manual for possible USART frame formats.
 276:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****       (++) USART polarity
 277:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****       (++) USART phase
 278:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****       (++) USART LastBit
 279:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****       (++) Receiver/transmitter modes
 280:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 281:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****   [..]
 282:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     The HAL_USART_Init() function follows the USART  synchronous configuration
 283:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     procedures (details for the procedures are available in reference manuals
 284:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c ****     (RM0008 for STM32F10Xxx MCUs and RM0041 for STM32F100xx MCUs)).
 285:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 286:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_usart.c **** @endverbatim
